  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='black' class='header'>ITEM COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>MELEE + ENCHANTER = DEATHWISH</font>, By Lasombra corazon</b><br><br>
<p>To the few posts that spoke of the meleeing enchanter who stands in there and takes the hits, I'd wager to say you are level 45 and lower...<br>
<br>
Enchanters, by definition, have the least ammt. of hitpoints of any and all classes. At 50 I barely clear 740hp before shields, so I too take the time to Augment myself for the Agi bonuses.<br>
<br>
But if any of you have hunted in places like Chardok, or City of Mist, where you have mobs that *average* double hitting for 117+, that thought of 'being right on in there' quickly dwindles after you throw up your first AE stun and you take a round of 110 x 6.<br>
<br>
So unless you're on a single mob, or unless you're rich enough to keep your Rune IV popped, the enchanter's role is to get in, AE stun, mez one, get out, repeat.<br>
<br>
The only real use I would find for the damage stats of this weapon is for fending off trash (killing skeletons and mummies that people train on you)</p>
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>ENCHANTER MELEE</font>, By Argothian mistweaver of xegony</b><br><br>I agree with Beldhyr jogues:
Of all the INT casters, we are the most capable of taking melee hits - and I make a point of it to get in there with the stuns.  I have no problem nuking at a safe distance with my fellow casters, but when 2 or 3 mob casters show up, I run into the middle of it all and use my aoe stun + melee attack (yup, I do mez when the situation calls for it).  Every few encounters, my defense skill still rises (yes, it's slow -- but at least my defense IS increasing) which makes me happy to take a few hits when needed.
Please, fellow enchanters: Don't let your Defense skill fall too far behind. You will be amazed at how the skill will save you someday!

<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>UPGRADE TODAY</font>, By Cylos</b><br><br>The patch message today states :'Increased the duration of the effect on the Enchanter Epic Quest Item. 'Don't know by how much, but I imagine Verant saw that casting this every 12 minutes got annoying pretty quick.

<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>ONLY LASTING 12 MINUTES.</font>, By Sinnaire</b><br><br>The buff is great in group, but on a raid. Having to recast this on every tank every 12 minutes would make me go crazy.  Plus, I wish they would make it the exact upgrade to augment, where it added ac too, Speed of shishar increased my agility 8 points than level 56 augment, but decreases my ac by over 20.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>MELEE</font>, By Tiiomon</b><br><br>I am a 36 Enchanter and NEVER melee, however, I always augment myself for the AGI and AC boast. More AC = Less HP losee. More AGI = More dodge. With 40AGI and 12ac, plus a 65% Haste, this will make you a favorite among tanks. <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
